# GitHub Actions, the on: section defines which events will trigger your workflow. The three you’re using are:

# push — runs when commits are pushed to the repository (branches or tags). Triggers when new commits are pushed.
# pull_request — runs when pull requests are opened/updated/closed (targeting specific base branches).
# workflow_dispatch — allows manual runs from the GitHub UI or via API, optionally with user-provided inputs.

# list of trigger types
#Manual               workflow_dispatch
#Scheduled            schedule 
#Code-related         push, pull_request, create
#Repo management      issues, labels, release
#Security             dependabot, dependency_review
